      "date": "2015-01-27 02:17:39.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHi Elena,\n\nCould you please improve the patch to address the comments from James?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "98ab1764f1f136271b53764d37fcef812f605b39",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 131,
        "name": "Jian Yu",
        "email": "yujian@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "yujian"
      },
      "date": "2015-01-27 02:17:59.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "92f685ed5c053b79704235495ee50a53817aa8eb",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 464,
        "name": "Elena",
        "email": "elena.gryaznova@hpe.com",
        "username": "elena"
      },
      "date": "2015-01-27 15:28:19.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> we don't need the \"-p\" option\nThis is incorrect statement. When test_mkdir() is called without -p option we have :\ntest_mkdir() {\n\n        case $# in\n                1) path=$1;;   # path=/mnt/lustre/d27i.sanity\n\n        child=$(basename $path) # child=d27i.sanity\n        parent=$(dirname $path) # parent=/mnt/lustre\n\n        if [ ! -d ${parent} ]; then # parent /mnt/lustre exist\n                if [ \"$p_option\" == \"-p\" ]; then\n                        mkdir -p ${parent}\n                else\n                        return 1\n                fi\n       fi\ni.e. if parent=/mnt/lustre exists -- \"mkdir\" is not called at all and the test fails because of $tdir is not created.\nJames, this is easy reproducible by:\n# sh llmount.sh\n# ONLY=27i sh sanity.sh",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "f3924da829e6c1aba04239c0559e065342a06f45",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 131,
        "name": "Jian Yu",
        "email": "yujian@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "yujian"
      },
      "date": "2015-01-28 23:54:53.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHi Elena,\n\nI tested \"test_mkdir $DIR/$tdir\" on the latest master branch and got:\n\n + test_mkdir /mnt/lustre/d27i.sanity\n + local option\n + local parent\n + local child\n + local path\n + local p_option\n + local option2\n + local stripe_count=2\n + local rc=0\n + case $# in\n + path=/mnt/lustre/d27i.sanity\n ++ basename /mnt/lustre/d27i.sanity\n + child=d27i.sanity\n ++ dirname /mnt/lustre/d27i.sanity\n + parent=/mnt/lustre\n + '[' '' == -p -o '' == -p ']'\n + '[' '' == -c ']'\n + '[' '' == -c ']'\n + '[' '!' -d /mnt/lustre ']'\n + '[' 1 -le 1 ']'\n + mkdir /mnt/lustre/d27i.sanity",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "462e4007dfa3498cac1513b467f6191741386ca0",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 292,
        "name": "James Nunez",
        "email": "jnunez@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jnunez"
      },
      "date": "2015-01-29 20:46:24.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: -Code-Review\n\nI’m running with lustre-master and I’ve added \"test_mkdir $DIR/d27\" (with no -p option), as the first line to sanity test 27i. When I run \n\n# sh llmount.sh\n# ONLY=27i sh sanity.sh\n\nit succeeds. I even tried with multiple MDSs (MDSCOUNT=2), but I can’t get this test to fail. \n\nDo you have any other details about your environment that could help us narrow down why this test fails without the “-p” option for you?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
